'''Fazyu Kardano''' nɣ '''Fazio Cardano''' (1444 - 28 ɣuct 1524), ikka t inn iga yan umsntam, amusnak, d yan unlmad n "perspective". Ikka t inn iga ula yan uslmad ɣ tɣiwant n Pavya, d yan umdan ittnaln taẓrhrmisit (hermétisme) d "occultisme". Ikka t inn iga ula yan umddakkl iɛzzan dar [[Lyunardu da Vintci|Lyunardu da Vinci]].

Ittwassn Kardano s mas t inn ikka da ittamẓ amsawal ɣar ntta d yixf nns, aydda yujjan tugt n mddn ad fllas ssufuɣn itsnt tfattalin d wumiyn, ɣ ttinin mas t inn ikka iɣy ad imsawaḍ d itsnt yiman/larwaḥ zɣ yimaḍaln yaḍnin.<ref>Payne, Robert (1978), ''Leonardo'', Doubleday, p. 95, <q>Probably, like many professors, he had a habit of talking to himself.</q></ref>

Iga Fazyu Kardano baba-s n [[Jirulanu Kardanu (Gerolano Cardano)|Gerolamo Cardano]].<ref>Alan Shuchat; Simon Gindikin. ''Tales of Mathematicians and Physicists''. Springer; 2007. <nowiki>ISBN 978-0-387-48811-0</nowiki>. p. 6.</ref>

